    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix measurement event processing in NR UE RRC\n\n### Summary\nThe NR UE RRC implementation was missing key components for handling measurement events, causing `start_meas_event()` to not behave as expected. When the UE received an RRC measurement procedure message, it would not properly initialize measurement events or set up the necessary data structures for ongoing measurement processing.\n\nThis fix adds the missing measurement-related data structures, implements the required functions for checking and triggering measurement events, and properly handles the RRC measurement procedure message.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR_UE/rrc_defs.h`: Added measurement-related fields (`measReportList`, `measTimer`, `HandoverInfoUe`) to `NR_UE_RRC_INST_t` structure and included `NR_MeasResults.h`\n- `openair2/RRC/NR_UE/rrc_proto.h`: Added function declarations for `nr_check_trigger_meas_event` and `nr_rrc_ue_generate_MeasurementReport`\n- `openair2/RRC/NR_UE/rrc_UE.c`: \n  - Implemented `nr_check_trigger_meas_event` function as a placeholder\n  - Implemented `nr_rrc_ue_generate_MeasurementReport` function as a placeholder\n  - Fixed the incomplete `RRC_MEASUREMENT_PROCEDURE` case to properly start measurement events\n  - Added periodic measurement processing in the `NRRRC_SLOT_PROCESS` case of the RRC task\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure an NR UE with measurement configuration\n2. Send an RRC measurement procedure message to the UE\n3. Observe that measurement events are not properly initialized and the UE does not process measurements as expected\n\nWith this fix, the measurement procedure will properly initialize and the UE will begin processing measurement events periodically.\n"
}